-- Comcast’s NBC Said to Gain $1.8 Billion in Ad Commitments
-- B y   A n d y   F i x m e r
-- 2012-06-13T23:16:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-13/comcast-s-nbc-said-to-gain-1-8-billion-in-ad-commitments.html
Comcast Corp. (CMCSA) ’s NBC broadcast
network collected about $1.8 billion in advertising commitments
for the television season starting in September, said a person
with knowledge of the situation.  NBC received $100 million more in orders than a year ago
after negotiating rate increases of 6 percent to 7 percent on
about 78 percent of its advertising inventory, said the person,
who wasn’t authorized to talk publicly.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andy Fixmer in Los Angeles at 
